subSubSection.paragraph:
Natives in many parts of the world catch this species for food, and there are cases of death reported upon consumption (
Ward, 1937
; 
Holthuis, 1968
; Wang & Liu, 1996; 
Ng, 1998
). Natives of some other places like the Pacific island of Su’uholo, regarded 

E. sebana

as a totem, whereby consumption of the crab is forbidden (
Ward, 1937
).

